Moses Sumney has a slightly different take on what is drily termed “aromanticism” – an imperviousness to coupling up.
That the swooning, layered backing vocals on many of these 11 tracks turn out to be just Sumney, multi-tracked, underscore his exquisite isolation.
Sometimes, Sumney considers, love founders on circumstance, or worse.
“Don’t call it a lovers’ quarrel,” demands Sumney.
Plastic – included here, but originally released in 2014 – finds Sumney sliding assuredly down the octaves on a single vocal line.